<br>
He sits politely to one side of the coffee shop, and places a few gold on the table, as he gestures to the server.  The server approaches, and he turns to her, scratching the back of his rat as it hisses at the waitress.<br>
<br>
&quot;My name is Timogen, and I am in need of some food for my companion.  Alespeis gets angry when she's hungry, but I can assure you she is well trained, and will not bite, or bring the Scourge to where we eat.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;And can I get you anything?&quot; she says, almost dreading the response, and certainly ready to leave, despite the generous offer of coin on the table.<br>
<br>
&quot;No thank you.  I bring my own beverage, and mind my own business.  The path of a Scourge Warrior is a lonely one.  You may take leave, but be sure to bring a few muffins for Alespeis to travel with.&quot;  He sips ale from a skull he had kept within a bag slung over his shoulder, and smoothly draws two weapons to polish his sword and knife with a grimy rag, as he lays his short staff aside.<br>
<br>
