<br>
Perhaps you are right.  But last time I tried to bring a soap cake near Alespeis, she got rather upset.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  Be that as it may, I at least have tried some underground streams outside of my home.  They should be somewhat fresher than that ones I normally frequent, although it seems that even on the moon the Plaugelord has his agents spreading rot.  Very different, though, from the festering boils that he tends to gift the sons and daughters of Qeynos with, but his work all the same.<br>
<br>
I am pleased to meet you though.  I can assure you that despite my smell, I am not contagious, as some of the scourge knights may be.  The death I bring is with staff and steel, and no mana has ever been gifted to me to spread the Plaguelord's will.<br>
